{
  "title": "Naive cynicism",
  "slug": "naive-cynicism",
  "publishedAt": "2020-07-05T06:39:33.000Z",
  "excerpt": "We’re all guilty of it.",
  "image": "",
  "readTime": "2 min",
  "content": [
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "We’re all guilty of it.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Convincing ourselves that our failure—as a culture, as a nation, as a genus—",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "is",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " the be all end all.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "That we’re done for, and there’s nothing much more we can do.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "To act like we know more than most. To strike a pose. To make up more reasons for giving up than trying.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Sure, pragmatism has its pros. We need to acknowledge the worse-case scenarios to know what’s worth fighting for. But optimism, faith in the human spirit, hope in a better outcome, and the conviction that collectively—",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "we can change this",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "—this stuff matters more.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "You can’t reach for a better scenario unless you can imagine one. And you can’t realize a better future unless you sacrifice something ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "now",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " to make it possible.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "I think we all need to be realistic. But convincing yourself that change is impossible or that the status quo is inevitable is ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "not",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " practical or objective. Giving up on the world is a perversion. And it doesn’t help anyone, including you.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Better, in my opinion, to put your faith in antiquity and tribes and facts. To recognize that change is not normally distributed, it starts ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "small",
          "marks": [
            "link-0"
          ]
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " and, over time, it ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "swells",
          "marks": [
            "link-1"
          ]
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " and catches on, infecting the rest of the group. Change is hard, but it’s not impossible, or ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "improbable",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": ".",
          "marks": []
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [
        {
          "_key": "link-0",
          "_type": "link",
          "href": "https://www.brainyquote.com/quotes/margaret_mead_100502"
        },
        {
          "_key": "link-1",
          "_type": "link",
          "href": "https://tinyurl.com/ydxdqvkp"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "We owe it to ourselves and our kids and theirs’ to make the best of our time on this planet. Or, at the very least, make the ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "absolute best",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " of the way things turn out.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
